				<name type="string">Painful Stare</name>
				<text type="formattedtext">
					<p>When an attack that deals damage hits the target of a mesmerist&#146;s hypnotic stare, the mesmerist can cause the target to take an amount of additional damage equal to 1/2 the mesmerist&#146;s class level (minimum 1). The mesmerist can use this ability as a free action, and can use it even if it isn&#146;t his turn. If the mesmerist uses this ability to increase his own damage, the additional damage increases by 1d6 points for every 3 class levels the mesmerist possesses. This damage is precision damage and is not multiplied on a critical hit. A mesmerist can trigger this ability only once per round, but a single creature can take damage from multiple mesmerists&#146; painful stares in a round.</p>
